nit: JSON isn't a proper noun.
So you are just squashing all the history?  Can we get reasons why?
We plan to use the upstream directly and not have to rely on downstream , so that any changes to associations can be picked up directly. So we are syncing downstream associations upstream
Please make this a name that matches a name on the CLA. (ie. Fix your git config)
Please address the commits from Patrick
These are not valid association names, right?

IMO, Following association should be used here.

rType: containing
fType: contained_by

For all chassis and inventory, the following should be used.

rType: containing
fType: contained_by

I still see at some places there is wrong association defined between inventory and chassis.
Please correct them.
This is not a valid association.

All slot to processor should have following association.
"rType": "connecting",
"fType": "connected_to"
Contains is not a valid association.Please update at all the required places.

contains in not a valid association type.
These needs to be corrected here and at all other places.
